)ATTR DEFAULT(%+_)

/******************************************************************************/
/*                                                                            */
/* NOTE:                                                                      */
/*    The above attribute defaults are equivalent to:                         */
/*                                                                            */
/*       )ATTR                                                                */
/*          % TYPE(TEXT)  INTENS(HIGH)                                        */
/*          + TYPE(TEXT)  INTENS(LOW)                                         */
/*          _ TYPE(INPUT) INTENS(HIGH)                                        */
/*                                                                            */
/******************************************************************************/

)BODY EXPAND(//)
%TUTORIAL/-/CUT and PASTE Help: Default Argument Values for CUT and PASTE/-/
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
%
%
+      The first time that you invoke either the%CUT+or the%PASTE+command,
+      you will be asked to supply the default  argument  values  that you
+      want to use for the commands.
+
+      These defaults allow you to run the%CUT+and%PASTE+commands  without
+      any arguments,  since the  default  values  will  be  automatically
+      substituted  for  any  arguments  that  you  do  not  specify  upon
+      invocation.
+
+      Later on,  you  may  review,  and  possibly  modify,  your  default
+      argument settings at any time,  by issuing either the %CUT DEFAULTS+
+      or  (equivalently)  the %PASTE DEFAULTS+ command.  Note  that  only
+      the first character position of the action argument is required, so
+      you may abbreviate the commands to%CUT D+or%PASTE D+respectively.
+
+
+                                                 (Continued on next page)
+
+
)PROC

   &ZCONT = CUTHLPD0
   &ZUP   = CUTHELP

)END
